race.comment: LAST DITCH EFFORT (8) was well fancied over 1200m at Cloncurry, beaten 2 lengths in Open grade. Came off a 9L win this track and trip in a 58 and he gets in well with the 2kg claim. The one to beat. NAPOLEON STRIKE (3) was in the placings at Richmond in a 65 and drops in the weights. Missed a whisker here prior in Open grade. Likely to push forward and will give a great sight. SWAMP NATION (4) is knocking on the door after just missing over 1200m at Cloncurry and at Richmond the one before. Expected to fight out the finish again. RESTRICTIONS (7) was in the placings at Richmond and should be prominent from the outset. Tumbles in weight and that gives him a chance.
